654
00:47:20,120 --> 00:47:23,715
All right, then, we'll be off.
Nice chatting with you.

655
00:47:28,400 --> 00:47:30,391
- He was very nice.
- Yeah.

656
00:47:42,600 --> 00:47:44,352
(Siren)

657
00:47:44,440 --> 00:47:47,398
- I think he's following us.
- Is he?!

658
00:47:48,480 --> 00:47:51,631
Ah, the police,
always wanting to play games.

659
00:48:04,560 --> 00:48:05,879
Ma'am!

660
00:48:40,640 --> 00:48:42,596
Is the little tree all right?

661
00:48:45,200 --> 00:48:46,758
Yeah, fine.

662
00:48:46,840 --> 00:48:48,478
(Maude) Terrific!

663
00:48:56,000 --> 00:48:57,752
(Patting the ground)

664
00:48:57,840 --> 00:48:59,796
(Maude) There.

665
00:48:59,880 --> 00:49:03,668
(Maude) Mmm! I love the feel of soil,
don't you?

666
00:49:04,200 --> 00:49:05,952
And the smell.

667
00:49:07,720 --> 00:49:09,472
It's the earth...

668
00:49:10,600 --> 00:49:14,991
The earth is my body,
my head is in the stars.

669
00:49:15,640 --> 00:49:17,710
Who said that?

670
00:49:19,000 --> 00:49:21,195
I don't know.

671
00:49:21,280 --> 00:49:23,191
I suppose I did.

672
00:49:23,280 --> 00:49:25,840
Oh, poor baby.

673
00:49:26,920 --> 00:49:31,118
Isn't it wonderful?!
All around us, living things.

674
00:49:39,480 --> 00:49:41,357
(Honks horn)

675
00:49:47,000 --> 00:49:48,991
(Siren)

676
00:50:33,520 --> 00:50:35,272
All right, out, lady.

677
00:50:36,960 --> 00:50:39,918
- Come on.
- Hello. Have we met before?

678
00:50:40,000 --> 00:50:41,797
None of that, lady. Out.

679
00:50:41,880 --> 00:50:45,998
It must have been your brother.
There is a family resemblance.

680
00:50:48,080 --> 00:50:51,755
Buddy, get out of the car.
Just stand over there, lady.

681
00:50:51,840 --> 00:50:53,398
Get out, buster!

682
00:50:53,480 --> 00:50:55,596
You're in a lot of trouble, lady.

683
00:50:55,680 --> 00:50:58,592
I have you for several offences,
including...

684
00:50:58,680 --> 00:51:00,716
possession of a stolen vehicle,

685
00:51:00,800 --> 00:51:04,475
resisting arrest and possession
of a stolen tree. Where is it?

686
00:51:04,560 --> 00:51:06,596
- We planted it.
- You planted it.

687
00:51:06,680 --> 00:51:08,750
- Is this your shovel?
- Er, no.

688
00:51:10,280 --> 00:51:12,316
Possession of a stolen shovel.

689
00:51:12,400 --> 00:51:15,597
Don't get officious.
You're not yourself when you are.

690
00:51:15,680 --> 00:51:17,955
That's the curse of a government job.

691
00:51:23,680 --> 00:51:25,238
Oh, lady.

692
00:51:27,480 --> 00:51:29,994
Are you gonna take
a lot of time with this?

693
00:51:30,080 --> 00:51:34,153
- Lady, please. Just quiet, please.
- Cos if you are...

694
00:51:39,160 --> 00:51:41,151
Grab the shovel, Harold.

695
00:51:51,240 --> 00:51:53,310
Lady! Stop or I'll have to shoot.

696
00:51:59,080 --> 00:52:00,832
(Clicks)

697
00:52:18,440 --> 00:52:20,351
I sure am picking up on vices.

698
00:52:21,480 --> 00:52:24,870
Vice? Virtue?
It's best not to be too moral.

699
00:52:24,960 --> 00:52:28,953
You cheat yourself out of
too much life. Aim above morality.

700
00:52:29,040 --> 00:52:31,952
If you apply that to life,

701
00:52:32,040 --> 00:52:34,235
then you're bound to live it fully.

702
00:52:40,760 --> 00:52:42,512
I haven't lived.

703
00:52:46,200 --> 00:52:48,111
I've died a few times.

704
00:52:48,200 --> 00:52:49,599
What was that?

705
00:52:51,120 --> 00:52:53,156
Well, er...

706
00:52:54,760 --> 00:52:58,992
The first time
was when I was at boarding school,

707
00:52:59,080 --> 00:53:00,832
in the chemistry lab.

708
00:53:00,920 --> 00:53:05,994
I was in there cleaning it up so I
decided I'd do a little experiment.

709
00:53:06,080 --> 00:53:09,993
You know, so I got all this stuff out
and began mixing it up,

710
00:53:10,080 --> 00:53:11,718
it was very scientific!

711
00:53:14,480 --> 00:53:16,869
There was this massive explosion.

712
00:53:16,960 --> 00:53:20,430
It knocked me down,
blew out a huge hole in the floor.

713
00:53:20,520 --> 00:53:24,832
There was boards and bricks
and flames leaping up.

714
00:53:24,920 --> 00:53:29,038
I figured, you know... time to leave.

715
00:53:29,120 --> 00:53:31,554
My career in school was over.

716
00:53:32,840 --> 00:53:35,991
So... I went home.

717
00:53:36,080 --> 00:53:40,676
My mother was a giving a party so
I went up the back stairs to my room.

718
00:53:41,760 --> 00:53:45,673
Turned out the light and,
er, I got this funny feeling.

719
00:53:47,760 --> 00:53:51,639
The doorbell rang.
I went out to the banister

720
00:53:51,720 --> 00:53:54,518
and these two policemen came in,

721
00:53:54,600 --> 00:54:00,232
found my mother... and... told her

722
00:54:00,320 --> 00:54:02,754
that I was killed in the fire.

723
00:54:03,680 --> 00:54:06,956
She put one hand up to her forehead,

724
00:54:07,040 --> 00:54:10,635
the other one she reached out
as if groping for support,

725
00:54:10,720 --> 00:54:15,748
and with this long sigh,
she collapsed

726
00:54:15,840 --> 00:54:17,637
in their arms.

727
00:54:45,400 --> 00:54:49,916
I decided right then
that I enjoyed being dead.

728
00:54:51,640 --> 00:54:55,918
I understand.
A lot of people enjoy being dead

729
00:54:56,000 --> 00:54:57,991
but they're not dead really.

730
00:54:58,080 --> 00:55:02,198
They're just backing away from life.

731
00:55:02,280 --> 00:55:07,559
Reach out and take a chance,
get hurt even,

732
00:55:07,640 --> 00:55:10,950
but play as well as you can.

733
00:55:11,040 --> 00:55:13,156
Go team, go!

734
00:55:13,560 --> 00:55:16,677
Gimme an L, gimme an I,
gimme a V, gimme an E.

735
00:55:16,760 --> 00:55:19,558
L-l-V-E, live.

736
00:55:21,200 --> 00:55:25,034
Otherwise you got nothing
to talk about in the locker room.

737
00:55:34,920 --> 00:55:36,478
I like you, Maude.

738
00:55:38,560 --> 00:55:40,357
I like you, Harold.

739
00:55:41,560 --> 00:55:43,790
