- What kind of car is it?

743
00:56:21,720 --> 00:56:24,393
- It's a little Jaguar.
- Oh.

744
00:56:26,480 --> 00:56:28,277
It looks like a hearse.

745
00:56:29,480 --> 00:56:31,755
Very nice. You know, compact.

746
00:56:31,840 --> 00:56:34,434
Edith, I'd like you to meet
my son Harold.

747
00:56:34,520 --> 00:56:36,192
Harold, this is Edith...

748
00:56:37,160 --> 00:56:40,152
- Phern.
- Phern. Very pleased to meet you.

749
00:56:40,240 --> 00:56:44,631
I think you should go and wash up,
dear. Join us in the drawing room.

750
00:56:45,680 --> 00:56:47,591
And what do you do, my dear?

751
00:56:47,680 --> 00:56:50,592
I'm a file clerk,
Harrison Feed and Grain.

752
00:56:50,680 --> 00:56:53,194
Well, what is it exactly that you do?

753
00:56:53,280 --> 00:56:56,636
I'm in charge of all the invoices
for the southwest.

754
00:56:56,720 --> 00:56:58,119
How interesting.

755
00:56:58,200 --> 00:57:01,829
We supply, for example,
most of the egg farmers in Pataluma.

756
00:57:01,920 --> 00:57:04,480
- So you can imagine...
- Yes.

757
00:57:06,520 --> 00:57:08,511
Oh, here's Harold now.

758
00:57:08,600 --> 00:57:10,511
Don't get up, dear.

759
00:57:16,440 --> 00:57:18,795
Edith has been talking about her job.

760
00:57:18,880 --> 00:57:20,438
I'm a file clerk.

761
00:57:20,520 --> 00:57:22,238
Henderson Feed and Grain.

762
00:57:22,320 --> 00:57:26,074
Harrison, Harrison Feed and Grain.
It's at Hamilton and 4th.

763
00:57:26,160 --> 00:57:27,991
I'm in charge of the invoices.

764
00:57:29,120 --> 00:57:31,634
I type up the schedule
for the trucking fleet.

765
00:57:31,720 --> 00:57:34,598
She supplies the whole southwest
with chicken feed.

766
00:57:34,680 --> 00:57:37,240
Well, not exactly
the whole southwest,

767
00:57:37,320 --> 00:57:39,515
although we do do a large business.

768
00:57:39,600 --> 00:57:43,149
Barley was very big last week.
1,500...

769
00:57:43,240 --> 00:57:45,196
bushels.

770
00:57:54,200 --> 00:57:56,156
(Phutters)

771
00:58:05,000 --> 00:58:07,275
In view of your recent actions,
Harold,

772
00:58:07,360 --> 00:58:09,396
you have left me with no recourse

773
00:58:09,480 --> 00:58:12,278
but to listen to
your uncle's proposed solution.

774
00:58:12,360 --> 00:58:17,388
Consequently, I have instructed him
to induct you into the service,

775
00:58:17,480 --> 00:58:19,596
and for your own good,

776
00:58:19,680 --> 00:58:23,559
to take up active duty
with the United States army.

777
00:58:24,600 --> 00:58:28,275
And I hope they have more luck
with you than I.

778
00:58:29,880 --> 00:58:32,872
Maude, they're gonna draft me.

779
00:58:32,960 --> 00:58:34,916
Well, don't go.

780
00:58:35,000 --> 00:58:36,877
They'll put me in jail.

781
00:58:36,960 --> 00:58:40,839
Well, historically,
you'll be in very good company.

782
00:58:44,960 --> 00:58:47,110
Maude, can you help me?

783
00:58:47,200 --> 00:58:52,115
With your skill and my experience, I
think we can come up with something.

784
00:58:53,760 --> 00:58:56,433
(Victor) Look on me
as a father in this matter.

785
00:58:56,520 --> 00:58:59,398
I know you have no desire
to join the army

786
00:58:59,480 --> 00:59:03,189
but once you're in, you'll love it.
It's a great life.

787
00:59:03,280 --> 00:59:07,398
Look at me - chauffeur, respect,
money in the bank.

788
00:59:08,640 --> 00:59:12,110
It has its drawbacks
like anything else, I suppose,

789
00:59:12,200 --> 00:59:17,149
but the army takes care of you
and you've got a buddy for life.

790
00:59:17,240 --> 00:59:19,435
(Whistling)

791
00:59:19,520 --> 00:59:23,069
Good idea coming out here, Harold.
It's a lovely spot.

792
00:59:23,160 --> 00:59:25,230
- Thank you, Uncle.
- Call me sir.

793
00:59:25,320 --> 00:59:29,916
That's the first thing you learn.
An officer deserves your respect.

794
00:59:30,000 --> 00:59:31,274
Yes, sir.

795
00:59:32,440 --> 00:59:34,396
Let's examine the facts on it.

796
00:59:35,720 --> 00:59:40,555
I say this country has been too harsh
in its outright condemnation of war.

797
00:59:40,640 --> 00:59:44,349
You can point to the many
material advantages brought about

798
00:59:44,440 --> 00:59:46,556
by a crisis and conflict policy.

799
00:59:46,640 --> 00:59:49,712
Hell, World War II gave us
the ballpoint pen.

800
00:59:49,800 --> 00:59:52,872
In wartime,
the national suicide rate drops.

801
00:59:52,960 --> 00:59:57,158
Is that a fact? Now, why in hell
did we give up on the Germans?

802
00:59:57,240 --> 01:00:00,994
Since the damn politicians
chalked them up on our side,

803
01:00:01,080 --> 01:00:04,470
the wars ever since
have been a national disgrace.

804
01:00:04,560 --> 01:00:06,039
Hell, look at history -

805
01:00:06,120 --> 01:00:09,669
the two best wars we ever
fought were against the Jerries.

806
01:00:09,760 --> 01:00:13,116
I say get the Krauts
on the other side where they belong.

807
01:00:13,200 --> 01:00:17,557
Let's have an enemy worth killing
and a war this country can support.

808
01:00:17,640 --> 01:00:20,632
Wow, that's pretty strong stuff, sir.

809
01:00:20,720 --> 01:00:24,759
Well, Harold, I've always been a man
that speaks his piece.

810
01:00:24,840 --> 01:00:28,515
Always hurt me.
I'm not liked in Washington.

811
01:00:28,600 --> 01:00:32,673
I know that...
but I do have friends in high places.

812
01:00:35,280 --> 01:00:38,670
(Victor imitating machine gun)
They kept falling!

813
01:00:38,760 --> 01:00:41,558
Joe falls back,
a neat, red hole in his head.

814
01:00:41,640 --> 01:00:45,519
(lmitates gun) Only one thing
kept going through my mind.

815
01:00:45,600 --> 01:00:50,549
Kill! Kill! For Joe and Mack
and all the rest of the guys.

816
01:00:50,640 --> 01:00:53,518
Kill! And then there was
a blinding flash...

817
01:00:58,040 --> 01:01:00,395
and I woke up on a stretcher.

818
01:01:04,320 --> 01:01:06,436
"Did we hold?" I asked the medic.

819
01:01:07,920 --> 01:01:09,512
"Yes, sir," he said...

820
01:01:13,920 --> 01:01:17,151
and I slipped into unconsciousness.

821
01:01:18,720 --> 01:01:22,872
Boy! Wow, that's a terrific story,
sir.

822
01:01:24,800 --> 01:01:29,555
Well, you'll have stories like that
to tell of your own some day.

823
01:01:29,640 --> 01:01:32,029
- Do you think so, sir?
- Sure you will.

824
01:01:32,120 --> 01:01:35,669
Gee, I never dreamed
it could be that exciting.

825
01:01:35,760 --> 01:01:38,399
It's the most exciting thing
in the world.

826
01:01:38,480 --> 01:01:41,756
To pit your own life against another.

827
01:01:41,840 --> 01:01:43,717
- Yes.
- To kill.

828
01:01:44,720 --> 01:01:47,109
The taste of blood in your mouth.

829
01:01:47,200 --> 01:01:49,191
The moment of truth.

830
01:01:49,280 --> 01:01:52,750
- Another man's life in your sights!
- Yes!

831
01:01:52,840 --> 01:01:56,753
- Will they really teach me to shoot?
- Sure. A range of weapons.

832
01:01:56,840 --> 01:01:59,434
- To use a bayonet?
- Yes!

833
01:01:59,520 --> 01:02:02,193
- How about hand-to-hand combat?
- Yes.

834
01:02:02,280 --> 01:02:04,316
To strangle someone, choke 'em,

835
01:02:04,400 --> 01:02:06,960
squeeze out his life
in your bare hands!

836
01:02:07,040 --> 01:02:10,396
- You're getting carried away.
- To slit his throat...

837
01:02:10,480 --> 01:02:13,040
- I don't know.
- See the blood spurt out.

838
01:02:13,120 --> 01:02:15,111
- And souvenirs.
- Souvenirs?

839
01:02:15,200 --> 01:02:18,670
Of your kill.
Eyes, ears, nose, scalp, privates.

840
01:02:18,760 --> 01:02:19,909
Harold!

841
01:02:20,000 --> 01:02:23,231
What would be the chance
of getting one of these?

842
01:02:23,320 --> 01:02:26,710
- To think I could make my own!
- That's disgusting.

843
01:02:26,800 --> 01:02:29,792
- It certainly is.
- Madam, who are you?

844
01:02:29,880 --> 01:02:33,270
- I am petitioning for peace.
- (Harold) Parasite.

845
01:02:33,360 --> 01:02:37,148
- I came here to speak.
- Crazy parasite. Commie bastard.

846
01:02:37,240 --> 01:02:41,677
Don't you talk to me like that,
you foul-mouthed degenerate.

847
01:02:41,760 --> 01:02:44,194
- Remember Nathan Hale.
- Calm down.

848
01:02:44,280 --> 01:02:47,875
- She's a commie pig...
- Don't you advance on me!

849
01:02:47,960 --> 01:02:50,633
- You'll all end up like this.
- Urgh!

850
01:02:50,720 --> 01:02:52,995
- Ooh, filth. Filth!
- Harold!

851
01:02:53,080 --> 01:02:56,152
Give me that.
I'm gonna throw that in the sewer.

852
01:02:56,240 --> 01:02:58,470
- Madam, please.
- She took my head.

853
01:02:58,560 --> 01:03:01,279
- Calm down, Harold.
- She took my head!

854
01:03:01,360 --> 01:03:03,794
- I'll kill her! I'll kill her!
- Harold!

855
01:03:03,880 --> 01:03:06,678
- I'll kill her!
- (Maude screaming)

856
01:03:06,760 --> 01:03:09,638
Give back the head,
let's have no trouble. Harold!

857
01:03:09,720 --> 01:03:12,678
- (Maude screaming)
- Madam! Harold!

858
01:03:12,760 --> 01:03:14,478
(Victor) Damn you!

859
01:03:14,560 --> 01:03:16,835
(All shouting)

860
01:03:16,920 --> 01:03:19,115
You took my head! You cow!

861
01:03:19,200 --> 01:03:21,156
- I'll kill you!
- Help!

862
01:03:21,240 --> 01:03:23,879
- Harold!
- I'll kill you.

863
01:03:23,960 --> 01:03:25,632
I'll kill you.

864
01:03:27,360 --> 01:03:29,476
Harold, stop that.

865
01:03:30,440 --> 01:03:31,395
Harold!

866
01:03:33,240 --> 01:03:35,276
(Splash)

867
01:03:51,120 --> 01:03:52,314
What have you done?

868
01:03:59,040 --> 01:04:00,871
- Maude?
- Hmm?

869
01:04:03,200 --> 01:04:04,997
Do you pray?

870
01:04:06,000 --> 01:04:09,117
Pray? No, I communicate.

871
01:04:10,480 --> 01:04:12,436
With God?

872
01:04:12,520 --> 01:04:14,158
Life.

873
01:04:18,240 --> 01:04:20,708
- (Harold) This is real nice.
- Yeah.

874
01:04:20,800 --> 01:04:24,076
- Makes me want to do somersaults.
- Why don't you?

875
01:04:24,160 --> 01:04:26,310
(Laughs) I'd feel stupid.

876
01:04:27,240 --> 01:04:31,358
Harold, everyone has the right
to make an ass out of themselves.

877
01:04:31,440 --> 01:04:34,591
You can't let the world
judge you too much.

878
01:04:45,600 --> 01:04:47,397
(Maude laughing)

879
01:04:53,200 --> 01:04:56,954
Er, do you care to join me
in a little cartwheel?

880
01:04:59,320 --> 01:05:01,390
I feel more like yelling!

881
