898
01:06:06,200 --> 01:06:07,553
Maude...

899
01:06:09,160 --> 01:06:12,118
I had the most wonderful day today...

900
01:06:12,200 --> 01:06:16,239
and... you're very beautiful.

901
01:06:18,680 --> 01:06:20,272
Oh, Harold!

902
01:06:20,360 --> 01:06:22,351
Ah!

903
01:06:22,440 --> 01:06:25,079
You make me feel like a schoolgirl.

904
01:06:33,880 --> 01:06:36,952
Shall I come and visit you tomorrow?
Oh, I can't.

905
01:06:37,040 --> 01:06:39,474
I have a luncheon date...

906
01:06:39,560 --> 01:06:40,913
with a girl.

907
01:06:42,560 --> 01:06:44,437
- Oh.
- I don't even know her.

908
01:06:44,520 --> 01:06:46,636
My mother arranged it.

909
01:06:50,320 --> 01:06:52,072
Oh, look!

910
01:06:52,160 --> 01:06:53,354
Oh!

911
01:06:54,480 --> 01:06:58,268
Dreyfus once wrote from
Devil's Island that he would see

912
01:06:58,360 --> 01:07:00,237
the most glorious birds.

913
01:07:00,320 --> 01:07:05,917
Many years later in Brittany, he
realised they had only been seagulls.

914
01:07:06,000 --> 01:07:08,309
# Ah ah ah, it's easy

915
01:07:09,240 --> 01:07:12,471
# Ah ah ah,
you only need to know... #

916
01:07:12,560 --> 01:07:16,109
For me, they will
always be glorious birds.

917
