921
01:07:28,720 --> 01:07:32,998
# You know that there are,
you know that there are

922
01:07:33,080 --> 01:07:36,117
# You know that there are #

923
01:07:40,480 --> 01:07:44,951
I cannot emphasise too strongly
the importance of this meeting.

924
01:07:45,040 --> 01:07:49,318
This is the last girl so this is
your third and final chance.

925
01:07:49,400 --> 01:07:52,119
And please try to be serious, Harold.

926
01:07:52,200 --> 01:07:54,953
If not for your sake,
at least for hers. Oh!

927
01:07:55,040 --> 01:07:56,871
There she is.

928
01:07:56,960 --> 01:07:59,520
Sunshine, I'd like you
to meet Harold.

929
01:07:59,600 --> 01:08:01,556
Harold, this is Sunshine Doré.

930
01:08:01,640 --> 01:08:03,676
How do... How do you do?

931
01:08:03,760 --> 01:08:05,671
Oh, I can't complain.

932
01:08:06,880 --> 01:08:08,916
Sunshine is an actress, Harold.

933
01:08:09,000 --> 01:08:11,673
- I like to think so.
- Hmm, wonderful.

934
01:08:11,760 --> 01:08:14,638
Why don't you two go down
to the music room

935
01:08:14,720 --> 01:08:17,109
and I'll follow with some drinks.

936
01:08:17,200 --> 01:08:19,953
Or perhaps Starlight
would like a cigarette.

937
01:08:20,040 --> 01:08:22,952
- Oooh, Sunshine!
- Oh, yes, of course.

938
01:08:23,040 --> 01:08:24,632
Sunshine.

939
01:08:42,560 --> 01:08:44,755
Would you like a cigarette?

940
01:08:44,840 --> 01:08:47,798
No, thank you. They stain my fingers.

941
01:08:47,880 --> 01:08:49,950
Is Sunshine your real name?

942
01:08:50,040 --> 01:08:55,034
Well, actually it was the name
of my drama teacher, Louis Sunshine.

943
01:08:55,120 --> 01:08:57,031
Perhaps you've heard of him?

944
01:08:57,120 --> 01:09:01,432
He was such an influence on
the development of my instrument.

945
01:09:01,520 --> 01:09:05,195
Er, that means my body
in theatre talk.

946
01:09:05,280 --> 01:09:07,555
Doré is my real name.

947
01:09:08,720 --> 01:09:11,712
Well, Dore, actually.

948
01:09:11,800 --> 01:09:16,316
Oh, my! What a lovely place
you have here.

949
01:09:17,680 --> 01:09:19,636
(Door creaking)

950
01:09:22,720 --> 01:09:24,551
(Continues creaking)

951
01:09:25,880 --> 01:09:27,438
Do you play?

952
01:09:27,520 --> 01:09:32,355
No. I am learning the ban...
The harmonica.

953
01:09:34,200 --> 01:09:36,634
Is this your father?

954
01:09:37,760 --> 01:09:40,069
No. It's my Uncle Victor.

955
01:09:40,160 --> 01:09:45,109
He's in the army. I do so like
the military, don't you?

956
01:09:46,800 --> 01:09:49,633
What a wonderful collection
of knives. May I see them?

957
01:09:49,720 --> 01:09:51,870
No, don't touch. They're very old.

958
01:09:51,960 --> 01:09:54,235
Do you enjoy knives?

959
01:09:54,320 --> 01:09:55,958
Oh, yes!

960
01:09:56,040 --> 01:09:58,838
You might find this one interesting.

961
01:09:59,840 --> 01:10:02,593
- It's a Hara-Kiri blade.
- (Giggles)

962
01:10:02,680 --> 01:10:04,238
What's Hara-Kiri?

963
01:11:09,040 --> 01:11:10,996
Whaaa!

964
01:11:12,200 --> 01:11:14,156
(Moaning)

965
01:11:15,520 --> 01:11:17,272
(Cries out)

966
01:11:18,840 --> 01:11:20,432
Hiraki!

967
01:11:27,880 --> 01:11:29,598
Oh!

968
01:11:31,040 --> 01:11:32,758
(Admiringly) Harold!

969
01:11:32,840 --> 01:11:35,957
Oh, that was marvellous!

970
01:11:37,040 --> 01:11:39,600
Oh, it had the ring of truth.

971
01:11:39,680 --> 01:11:44,231
I played Juliet
in the Sunshine Playhouse.

972
01:11:44,320 --> 01:11:46,880
Louis thought it was
my best performance.

973
01:11:50,040 --> 01:11:54,511
What's here?
A cup, closed in my true love's hand?

974
01:11:54,600 --> 01:11:56,795
(Sniffing)

975
01:11:56,880 --> 01:12:01,670
Poison, I see,
hath been his timeless end.

976
01:12:02,720 --> 01:12:05,871
O, happy dagger.

977
01:12:07,160 --> 01:12:09,958
O, happy dagger,

978
01:12:10,040 --> 01:12:14,079
this is thy sheath,
there rest... (Gags)

979
01:12:14,160 --> 01:12:18,153
...and let me die... (Moans)

980
01:12:23,840 --> 01:12:26,195
I-I've...

981
01:12:39,520 --> 01:12:42,193
Oh! Harold!

982
01:12:47,280 --> 01:12:49,635
That was your last date.

983
01:12:56,200 --> 01:12:57,838
(# Fairground organ)

984
01:13:24,680 --> 01:13:26,875
(Harold) It wasn't very scary.

985
01:13:26,960 --> 01:13:29,713
No. It had nothing on this afternoon.

986
01:13:29,800 --> 01:13:33,475
Oh, come on, you loved it.
It was a new experience.

987
01:13:33,560 --> 01:13:35,357
(Maude laughs)

988
01:14:11,760 --> 01:14:13,716
(All laughing and cheering)

989
01:14:29,600 --> 01:14:32,672
(Harold) You sure have a way
with people.

990
01:14:32,760 --> 01:14:34,796
Well, they're my species.

991
01:14:38,840 --> 01:14:41,434
- (Harold) Look at these stars.
- Mmm.

992
01:14:45,520 --> 01:14:47,954
- Maude...
- Yes?

993
01:14:55,480 --> 01:14:56,833
Here.

994
01:14:58,240 --> 01:14:59,878
A gift!

995
01:15:06,080 --> 01:15:08,116
"Harold loves Maude"

996
01:15:13,560 --> 01:15:15,755
And Maude loves Harold.

997
01:15:19,480 --> 01:15:24,395
This is the nicest present
that I've received in years.

998
01:15:30,880 --> 01:15:32,632
(Splash)

999
01:15:34,600 --> 01:15:37,592
So I'll always know where it is.

1000
